# WORK PROCESS

### **CREATE NEW COMPANY** (STEP BY STEP) Google **Search by Company**

1. **If the company doesn‚Äôt exist in CRM, add**: the name of the company, Company LinkedIn, Website, Size, and Industry (Company Size is how many employees work in the company)

2. #### Find leads from the company. Use a scheme of **search by positions**, paste the name of the company

3. Add leads, **try to add as more as you can** (It‚Äôs your chance for doing more calls)  
4. 	   **Save card**. Write to leads \=\> **connect**  
5.      **Change status** in the CRM-system

#### COMMENT

1. **Add companies from your country**, if your country is Poland, but you add from Austria, it is not OK\!  
2. **Company Size is how many employees work in the company**

3. #### If 150 employees are working in a company, but you add 1 employee, it's not ok, you should find and add at least 2 people

4. **Hindus, Arabs, color skinned people are not allowed to add (exception: if African Americans are located in the country with which we work and hold leadership positions, then in some cases it is possible to assign calls with them).**

# WORK PROCESS

### **UPDATE COMPANY IN CRM** 

We are updating the information of companies that were added by you or someone else more than three months ago. We write repeated messages to the leads of such companies and send a repeated connection.

In order to find such companies in CRM, go to the LEADS tab, in the filters located to the left of the list of all leads, select the required fields:

* Country \- the country with which you are currently working  
* Lead Status field \- lead status, work with all statuses, except for the Call status (this status means that our company has already called this lead) and the not relevant status. Also skip leads marked ‚Äúclient‚Äù.

And click Apply

You will receive a list of companies that have been included in CRM for all time, under the status that you choose and specifically for your country. Go to the last page of the list and open companies.

Next, edit the information in the lead card in CRM  
**1\)** Enter your details in the Active Agents field.  
**2\)** In the LinkedIn Accounts field, choose your account from which the connection was sent.  
**3\)** Change the status to **Sent Request**  
**4\)** **Check and add** in CRM all information about the company from LinkedIn, add new leads, remove leads who are already not work in the company  
**5\)** Leave a comment in Note \- **updated**  
**And click update.**

##### **Lead Status Change:**

[Change Lead Status \- remote helpers blog (rh-s.com)](http://blog.rh-s.com/izmenenie-statusa-lida/)  
**Sent request** \- Default status,  sets when new Lead addes to CRM.  
**Connected** \- sets when Lead connected to you on LinkedIn.  
**Interested** \- sets when Lead answered .  
**Not interested** \- sets when Lead is definitely not interested in our services.  
**Ignoring** \- sets when Lead disappears after you almost agreed for a call.  
**Follow up** \- sets when Lead ask to text him later and tell you at least abstract time when to text him again(‚ÄúI'm busy right now text me in July/the end of the year/few weeks/etc‚Äù  
**Event(LG manager main goal)** \- sets when Lead booked a call.
